HEADWORD: Torpent
<hw>Tor"pent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>torpens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>torpere</ets> to be numb.]</ety>
<def>Having no motion or activity; incapable of motion; benumbed;
torpid.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

